                     Guide for Developing Security Plans for Federal Information Systems


Appendix B: Glossary

COMMON TERMS AND DEFINITIONS


Accreditation        The official management decision given by a senior agency official
[NIST SP 800-37]     to authorize operation of an information system and to explicitly
                     accept the risk to agency operations (including mission, functions,
                     image, or reputation), agency assets, or individuals, based on the
                     implementation of an agreed-upon set of security controls.
Accreditation        All components of an information system to be accredited by an
Boundary             authorizing official and excludes separately accredited systems, to
[NIST SP 800-37]     which the information system is connected. Synonymous with the
                     term security perimeter defined in CNSS Instruction 4009 and DCID
                     6/3.
Accrediting          See Authorizing Official.
Authority
Adequate             Security commensurate with the risk and the magnitude of harm
Security             resulting from the loss, misuse, or unauthorized access to or
[OMB Circular A-     modification of information.
130, Appendix III]
Agency               See Executive Agency.
Authentication       Verifying the identity of a user, process, or device, often as a
                     prerequisite to allowing access to resources in an information
                     system.
Authenticity         The property of being genuine and being able to be verified and
                     trusted; confidence in the validity of a transmission, a message, or
                     message originator. See authentication.
Authorize            See Accreditation.
Processing
Authorizing          Official with the authority to formally assume responsibility for
Official             operating an information system at an acceptable level of risk to
[NIST SP 800-37]     agency operations (including mission, functions, image, or
                     reputation), agency assets, or individuals.
Availability         Ensuring timely and reliable access to and use of information.
[44 U.S.C., Sec.
3542]




